fix: planet state_patch so UI sees new planets without reload

Bug: Reyes Genesis-deployed Wyrd 238-19 on day 2 but the spectator UI
never showed the planet on his commander card. Investigation: the
client populates state.planets ONLY from the initial snapshot; live
state_patch frames only carried patch.player, so any planet created
mid-match was invisible until F5.

Fix:
- server/runner.py: GENESIS_DEPLOYED, ASSIGN_COLONISTS, BUILD_CITADEL,
  and CITADEL_COMPLETE events now ship a `planet` field in the
  state_patch with the full planet snapshot.
- web/app.js: onEvent() merges patch.planet into state.planets, same
  shape as patch.player -> state.players. Drawer, sector tooltips,
  and the commander-card Planets block all update on the next render
  tick without a reload.

Tests: +2 regressions in TestPhaseKPlanetPatch (151/151 pass).